<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1129">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BGW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Buckner</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-07">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1914</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Strongly recommend to Liberian Government that President issue neutrality
                            proclamation at once if he has not already done so.<note n="2" xml:id="d1129fn1">The proclamation was issued August 10, 1914 (File
                                No. 763.72111N39/21).</note> Department has asked British, French,
                            and German Governments to give assurance that neutrality of Liberia will
                            be respected.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>